HEADWORD: Nitromuriatic
<hw>Ni`tro*mu`ri*at"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>nitromuriatique</ets>. See <er>Nitro-</er>, and
<er>Muriatic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
composed of, nitric acid and muriatic acid; nitrohydrochloric. See
<er>Nitrohydrochloric</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
